<br>
I can’t help but question it giving them the “same” liberties that it gives me.  It seems as if it is giving them extra liberties.  If I am killed my killer gets one term, where their killer would get much more.  What makes their life more valuable? The fact that they believe something or that they were born somewhere different than me?  Isn’t that giving a bit of preference?<br>
<br>
If a man kills his wife because she was cheating and she believed that adultery was okay, then he has killed someone in the minority right?  I don’t mean to sound stupid, and forgive me if I do, I am just trying to make sense of this.  <br>
<br>
