<br>
I guess that either way you go the question becomes where do you draw the line, and if the line is a grey matter and not black/white then how can we guarentee the rights of a criminal.  Criminals do have rights... and those rights can't be given or taken on a whim.  They have to be equal for all right?<br>
<br>
If someone is gay, it isn't a statement.. it isn't a right.  Living is a right.  Living how you want is a right.  Gay, straight, etc.  <br>
<br>
Killing someone isn't a statement, it is a crime.  Some people live in such a way that they try to make a statement, but in the end... its either life or death right?<br>
<br>
You take a life, or you don't.<br>
<br>
